headline: Johnson & Johnson reinstated with a Neutral at BofA
summary: BofA reinstated coverage of Johnson & Johnson with a Neutral rating and $166 price target The current valuation at a premium to other drug names “seems likely to cap upside,” the analyst tells investors while reinstating coverage of 11 large-cap U.S. pharma and biotech stocks. J&J has a “fairly interesting pipeline” and talc litigation resolution in 2025 “would help,” the analyst added.
